Total Crypto Market Cap Desc: Total market value of all cryptocurrency's circulating supply in the market.
Stablecoin Total Market Cap Desc: Stablecoins can be realized as a foundational asset class within the digital asset ecosystem, acting as the quote asset for many trade transactions.Note: An increase/decrease in the total stablecoin market cap can be seen as a sign of money flowing into/out of the crypto market
Active Address on Chains Desc: The number of unique addresses that were active on the BTC network either as a sender or receiver.
Transactions on Chains Desc: The total amount of transactions. A successful transaction that is recorded and can be confirmed over a blockchain.
BTC Hashrate Desc: Bitcoin hashrate, also known as computing power, is the total amount of computational power that is being used to mine and process transactions on a Proof-of-Work blockchain, such as Bitcoin. The more hashing power in the network, the greater its security and its overall resistance to attack.
BTC Mining difficulty Desc: BTC mining difficulty is a measure of how difficult it is to mine a new block on the Bitcoin network. It is adjusted every 2016 blocks (approximately every two weeks) to ensure that blocks are found at a consistent rate of one every 10 minutes. The difficulty is determined by the total computational power of the network, with higher difficulty levels requiring more computational power to mine new blocks.
